main event: A UFO was observed emitting flashes every 20 seconds on 3 October 1965.
interesting points: The object was off the horizon and was observed for about 10 minutes., The flashes were considered to be from a photo mapping camera on an aircraft., No radar contact was made during the observation., The estimated speed of the object was 920 knots if it was at 45,000 feet., The sighting occurred over a US aircraft with no flight plan in the area.
witnesses: pilot and flight engineer of an EC-121D aircraft
